PUH-BrianMartell LIGO Ringdown Data Anomalies  Understandable Analysis LIGO/Virgo/KAGRA gravitational wave detections of black hole mergers include a ringdown phase  the final merged hole settles with damped oscillations (quasi-normal modes, QNM) predicted by GR. Current status (up to early 2026 data):   Over 200 events analyzed (GWTC catalogs + O4 run).   Ringdown tests (e.g., GW250114, loudest signal Jan 2025) show strong consistency with GR  frequencies/damping match no-hair theorem.   Overtone detections in high-SNR events (e.g., fundamental + higher modes) but no significant deviations.   Anomalies debated: Slight overtone mismatches or noise artifacts in some events, but mostly ruled as consistent or low-significance.   No major GR-breaking anomalies yet  constraints tightening on modifications. In PUH v25, ringdown is mechanical oscillation of yield surface ( = _yield frozen braids)
